## Hardcoded Client-Server Contracts (DO NOT CHANGE)

### HTTP Headers
```
X-Token          → Session token (dalogin → all services)
X-HMAC-HASH      → HMAC-SHA512(body + secret)
X-Device         → Device identifier (iOS client → mbooks)
Ciphertext       → Encrypted body (iOS → dalogin, mbooks)
uuid             → Device UUID (client → dalogin)
TIME_            → Timestamp (HMAC calculation)
XSRF-TOKEN       → CSRF protection (dalogin)
```

### Payment Checkout Flow
```
POST /login/CheckOut with {
  payment_method_nonce: "...",
  orderId: "...",
  seatsToBeReserved: "A1-B2-C3-"  // seat numbers, NOT IDs
}
```

### API Endpoints
```
POST   /login/HelloWorld                    → HMAC login
GET/POST /login/CheckOut                    → Payment gateway
GET    /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies           → Movie listing
GET    /mbooks-1/rest/book/payment/clientToken
POST   /mbooks-1/rest/book/payment/fullcheckout2
WS     /mbooks-1/ws                         → Real-time seat updates
GET    /simple-service-webapp/rest/images/* → Image serving
```

### Braintree SDK Versions (Sandbox)
```
JavaScript: 1.44.1
iOS:        5.26.0
Java:       3.36.0
Merchant:   j3ndqpzrhy4gp2p7
```

## Key Architectural Patterns

### 1. Dual Database Schemas
- **login_** — User credentials, devices, sessions, vouchers (dalogin primary)
- **book** — Movies, venues, screens, seats, tickets, purchases (mbooks direct access)

### 2. Pessimistic Locking for Seats
```
SELECT seats FOR UPDATE (pessimistic write lock)
  ↓
Verify availability (seat.isReserved == "0")
  ↓
Create tickets + purchase
  ↓
Braintree transaction
  ↓ (failure) → ROLLBACK: delete tickets+purchase, free seats
  ↓ (success) → COMMIT: mark seats reserved
```

### 3. Microservice Header Injection
- dalogin acts as auth gateway
- ServiceClient injects pre-authenticated headers to downstream services
- All services read X-Token from request (no re-auth needed)

### 4. iOS Service Layer Refactoring
- Modern async/await + centralized APIClient
- Endpoint descriptor pattern (path, method, query, body, cache key)
- HeaderProvider protocol with multiple auth implementations
- Service injection via AppDelegate → UIViewController extensions

## Common Tasks & Their Locations

### Adding a Payment Feature
→ Start: `mbooks-quarkus/src/main/java/com/jeet/rest/BookController.java` (line 600–1170)
→ Braintree: `service/PaymentService.java`
→ Lock logic: `db/DAO.java` (`bookTickets()` method)

### Fixing Web UI Payment
→ Start: `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review/`
→ Interceptor: `app.js` (HMAC calculation)
→ Template: `checkout.html`
→ Note: Check header names haven't changed (X-HMAC-HASH, etc.)

### Fixing iOS Service Call
→ Start: `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Networking/BackendServices.swift`
→ Endpoint: `Endpoint.swift`
→ Headers: `HeaderProvider.swift` (SessionHeaderProvider, HMACLoginHeaderProvider, etc.)
→ URL config: `URLManager.swift`

### Adding iOS UI Test
→ Start: `appium/src/test/java/qa/ios/test/TestNavigations.java`
→ Pages: `appium/src/test/java/qa/ios/pages/`
→ Run: `.run/appium - mvn test`

### Deploying to Kubernetes
→ Build: `./mvnw -s k8infra/settings-local.xml package -DskipTests`
→ Images: `docker build -t servicename:local ./servicename-quarkus`
→ Deploy: `kubectl apply -f k8infra/quarkus-backend.yaml`
→ Tunnel: `sudo minikube tunnel`

## Common Issues & Solutions

### Payment fails on Web but works on iOS
- [ ] Check `POST /login/CheckOut` parameter format (seatsToBeReserved)
- [ ] Verify HMAC interceptor includes correct headers
- [ ] Compare Braintree SDK version (JS 1.44.1)
- [ ] Check Apache ProxyPass preserves Content-Type

### WebSocket disconnects
- [ ] Verify `sudo minikube tunnel` is running
- [ ] Check WebSocket ProxyPass **comes before** HTTP routes in Apache
- [ ] Confirm Sec-WebSocket-Key header in browser dev tools
- [ ] Check Quarkus WebSocket registration (mbook-quarkus pom.xml)

### Session not found
- [ ] Verify CookieFilter registered in web.xml (before AuthFilter)
- [ ] Check cookie domain (localhost vs 127.0.0.1)
- [ ] Confirm ActiveVoucherFilter runs after CookieFilter
- [ ] Validate session in MySQL `session_login` table

### Stale seat availability
- [ ] Confirm DAO.getSeatsForScreening() NOT using query cache
- [ ] Verify L2 cache evicted after mutation (`cache.evictRegion("ticket")`)
- [ ] Check FetchType.EAGER on bidirectional relationships

### Images not loading on iOS
- [ ] Verify simple-service-webapp running on port 8085
- [ ] Check URLManager.swift resolves absolute paths
- [ ] Confirm Apache ProxyPass includes /simple-service-webapp
- [ ] Verify PVC mounted (k8infra/quarkus-backend.yaml)

## Development Workflow

### One-Time Setup
```bash
# 1. Review constitution
cat .specify/memory/constitution.md

# 2. Build backend services
./mvnw -s k8infra/settings-local.xml package -DskipTests

# 3. Deploy to Minikube (in separate terminal)
eval $(minikube docker-env)
docker build -t dalogin:local ./dalogin-quarkus
# ... build other images ...
eval $(minikube docker-env --unset)
kubectl apply -f k8infra/quarkus-backend.yaml

# 4. Keep tunnel running (separate terminal)
sudo minikube tunnel
```

### Edit → Test → Deploy
```bash
# Edit code in IDE
# Run test config from .run/ directory
# OR manually: mvn test -f service-name/pom.xml -s k8infra/settings-local.xml

# Rebuild & redeploy
./mvnw -s k8infra/settings-local.xml package -DskipTests
docker build -t servicename:local ./servicename-quarkus
kubectl rollout restart deployment/servicename
```

### Run Test Suites
```bash
# iOS UI tests
mvn test -f appium/pom.xml -s k8infra/settings-local.xml

# Python API tests
python k8infra/test-login.py

# Direct TestNG
cd appium && java -cp target/test-classes:target/classes:...libs/* org.testng.TestNG testng.xml
```

## IntelliJ Run Configurations

All `.run/` configs are pre-configured:
- `dalogin - package` — Build dalogin JAR
- `mbooks - quarkus:dev` — Dev mode with live reload
- `appium - mvn test` — iOS UI tests via Surefire
- `appium - java direct (testng)` — Direct TestNG
- `appium - CreateXml GUI` — Swing test suite builder
- `ALL - package (skip tests)` — Build all 4 services
- `k8s - test-login.py` — Python API smoke tests

**Note:** Maven configs use `myGeneralSettings` → `k8infra/settings-local.xml` for proxy bypass.

## Observability

### Prometheus
- Endpoint: All services expose `/metrics` (Quarkus default)
- Scrape: Configured in `k8infra/quarkus-backend.yaml`
- Key metrics: `http_requests_total`, `jvm_memory_used_bytes`, `db_connection_pool_active`
- Retention: 15 days

### Grafana
- **Service Health:** HTTP rate, p95 latency, 5xx errors (per service)
- **JVM:** Heap memory, threads, GC pause times (per service)
- **Database:** Connection pool, slow queries, replication lag
- Data source: `http://prometheus:9090`

### Tempo
- Trace collection: OpenTelemetry exports to Tempo
- Query UI: Grafana Tempo plugin (`https://localhost:3000/explore`)
- Service graph: Auto-generated from trace metadata
- Retention: 48 hours

